physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Pectus excavatum, large anterior fontanel, rachitic skeletal changes (rachitic rosary), low serum alkaline phosphatase (75 U/liter; normal range, 250-1000 U/liter), high urinary phosphoethanolamine (440 μmol/liter; normal range, 0–78 μmol/liter), elevated serum inorganic phosphorus level (2.38 mmol/liter; normal range, 1.30–2.20 mmol/liter).
First traumatic fracture of left metacarpal.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Since this initial fracture at age 8, subsequent fractures occurred in both tibia and left femur, leading to surgical treatment by internal fixation.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: No developmental delay has been observed.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Growth declined to below average during childhood.
